## Known Issues (from manual + code review)

| ID | Area | Description |
|---|---|---|
| RET-011 | FIX retrieval | `what is tag 22` returns tag details + all enums. Should be focused unless enums explicitly requested. |
| RET-010 | Structured planner | Ranking balance for phrases like "executing broker" in long descriptions. |
| CODE-001 | query_router.py | `client.scroll(limit=5000)` in 4 lexical search functions — full collection scan in Python, not indexed. |
| CODE-002 | query_router.py | `if collection == "obsidian":` hardcoded collection name check. |
| CODE-003 | query_router.py | Qdrant client instantiated at module import time — system fails to start if NAS unreachable. |
| CODE-004 | query_router.py | `run_query_with_method` and `route_query` overlap in logic and are not fully in sync. |
| CODE-005 | xml_serializer.py | Function-level state (`_all_rows`, `_files_seen`) for cross-file buffering — corrupts silently on crash. |
| CODE-007 | collection_state | Deleting a Qdrant collection does NOT clear `config/collection_state/<name>.json`. Files are skipped on next ingest as "unchanged". Workaround: manually delete the state file before re-ingesting. Permanent fix: move state to PostgreSQL in Phase 2. |

