## Smoke Test Results

### FIX Smoke Test — Baseline (2026-06-09)  **4/6 passed**

| ID | Question | Method used | Pass? | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| FIX-01 | what is tag 22 | structured_namespace_lookup | ❌ FAIL | RET-011: returns 19 enum lines unprompted. Answer itself is correct, just too much. |
| FIX-02 | what values can tag 22 have | structured_namespace_lookup | ✅ PASS | Correct — enums requested, enums returned |
| FIX-03 | what tag is exec broker | structured_query_plan | ✅ PASS | Contains "76" — but answer preview shows RoundingDirection first, not ExecBroker. Needs review. |
| FIX-04 | what tag is execution broker | structured_query_plan | ✅ PASS | Same concern as FIX-03 — passes because "76" appears, but top result is wrong |
| FIX-05 | what tag can have a value ISIN | structured_query_plan | ❌ FAIL | Answer shows SecurityIDSource (correct!) but "ISIN" not in text. Answer format drops enum detail. |
| FIX-06 | what tags contain security | structured_query_plan | ✅ PASS | Good — returns correct discovery list |

**Observations:**
- FIX-03 and FIX-04 pass only because "76" appears somewhere in the answer — the top result shown is actually RoundingDirection, not ExecBroker. These are **false passes**. Smoke test needs stricter checks.
- FIX-01 failure is pure RET-011: correct data, wrong verbosity.
- FIX-05 failure: the answer finds the right tag (SecurityIDSource / Tag 22) but drops the enum value detail "ISIN" from the output format.